Naive Brute force takes O(M*N)

KMP algorithm preprocesses pat[] and constructs an auxiliary lps[] of size m (same as the size of the pattern)
which is used to skip characters while matching.
Name lps indicates the longest proper prefix which is also a suffix. 
A proper prefix is a prefix with a whole string not allowed. 
For example, prefixes of “ABC” are “”, “A”, “AB” and “ABC”. Proper prefixes are “”, “A” and “AB”. 
Suffixes of the string are “”, “C”, “BC”, and “ABC”.


Take i - pointer for text string
Take j - pointer for pattern string

Keep LPS ready  (size of the pattern string)

Start moving i and j - see video to understand more 

Start comparing the main text string and the pattern string 

In case of mismatch - move j to the index = number stored in LPS[i]

If there is no movement for j left (it reached the beginning = 0...) - 
leave this and increment i and start comparing again

So - we have never moved i backwards. It just loops through the main text string once

